Navigate through the surface of a hypersphere and kill your enemies.

* Use `git clone --recursive` to clone with submodules.

* Necessary packages (used in Debian 6, Ubuntu 11.04, Mint 12):
  build-essential
  automake (This and below only if you do not have "configure" script generated)
  autoconf
  libtool
  libgl1-mesa-dev
  libglew1.5-dev
  libsdl2-dev
  libboost-dev
  libopenal-dev
  libopusfile-dev

-> Debian and Ubuntu users:
sudo apt-get install build-essential automake autoconf libtool libgl1-mesa-dev libglu1-mesa-dev libglew1.5-dev libsdl2-dev libboost-thread-dev libboost-system-dev libguichan-0.8.1-1v5 libguichan-opengl-0.8.1-1v5 libguichan-sdl-0.8.1-1v5 libguichan-dev libopenal-dev libopusfile-dev

* Optional packages:
  Doxygen
  python3-gobject
  blender 2.59+

* Generate configuration files:
  $ ./autogen.sh

* Compile:
  $ ./configure
  $ make -j

* Enable stats tunning:
  $ CXXFLAGS="-DSTATS_TUNNING" ./configure
  $ make -j

* Generate documentation:
  $ make doxygen-doc

* Play:
  $ cd src/sdl
  $ ./glome
